Text: Sorry, this is all I have.

The soldiers confiscated all the valuable stuff like
coffee, claiming they needed it for war...

The main street? What was once an idyllic cityscape
has now been reduced to rubble...

I'm afraid you picked a bad time to get stuck here,
Cid. I only just opened this tavern myself...

(After parting ways with Delta, I wandered aimlessly,
giving myself time to reflect.)

(For starters, the whole point of my journey was
finding myself.)

(Up until now, in various situations, I acted as if I
were some kind of shadowbroker...)

(But, looking back, I never had a clear image of what
a shadowbroker is.)

(I guess I was content as long as I did something
that sort of seemed to fit the bill at the time.)
(Should I really be continuing down this path?)
(Why do I feel like something is missing?)
I'm not sure things are okay like this...
Of course...it's not okay.
We mustn't give up.
We must never give up...
Here you go.
Thank you!
Wait, that's mine—
Ahh!
Hey!

Didn't your grandmother ever teach you not to eat
other people's food?
I-I'll prepare another one right away...
Miss! I'd like one without parsley.
You still want to eat more?!
I've got to do something about this...
...Sorry.
I'm sorry...!

Sometimes, people realize when they're having a
dream. For Rose Oriana, it always happens at the
same moment.
Her father is standing before her.

Rose stabs her blade into her father. Slowly but
surely, slowly but surely.

She can't stop it. She can't pull it back. Time just
flows forward, cruel in its slowness and its surety.
Ro...se...
F-Father—
...will never...
...forgive you.
I'm sorry...
*gasp*
Father...

What had her father tried to say to her on that
fateful day?

Had he resented her? Had he hated her? Were those
words he spoke in her nightmare truly how he felt?

Oriana's castle town, Fort First... It used to be
such a beautiful place.

Not even this town...could escape the flames of
war...

I felt as though joining the Shadow Garden would let
me start changing things... I felt that if I became
strong, I could save the Oriana Kingdom...
Just then, there's a knock on the door.
No. 666, it's time.
Come on, come on!
On my way.

No. 664 is a petite elf a year older than Rose.
She's strict but responsible, which is why she
was chosen as a squad leader.

No. 665 is an elf with a lazy streak who's the same
age as Rose. She always looks like she's about to
doze off.

Not only are they both attractive, but each of them
would be a first-rate dark knight by most standards.
Within their organization, however, both of them are
closer to the bottom of its rankings than to the top.

The numbers refer strictly to the order in which they
joined. They aren't a ranking system.

However, each set of 100 tends to be a good deal
stronger than the next, so the numbers end up
being a decent measure anyway.
Today's mission will be led by No. 559.
No. 559. You mean...HER?

Yeah, the powerhouse who defeated No. 89 and earned
the right to challenge the Numbers.
Powerhouse...

Rose felt like her magic had gotten stronger. She
felt as though joining the Shadow Garden would let
her start changing things. She felt that if she
became strong, she could save the Oriana Kingdom.
But she hasn't been able to change anything.
(I need to work even harder...)

If there's something weighing on you, you should tell
me about it.
No...it's nothing.
...If you say so.
Three with sauce, Ma'am!
At least try and show a little concern!
Relax, it's time for some sightseeing now!
Scouting, not sightseeing...
